<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>SPICER 14-INCH (355.6 MM) STAMPED ANGLE-SPRING CLUTCH - TWO PLATE CLUTCH REMOVAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>TWO PLATE CLUTCH REMOVAL</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>TRANSMISSION REMOVAL</title>
            <para>A sling or jack supporting the transmission and drive shaft during removal helps maintain alignment.
                Do not let the rear of the transmission drop, or let the transmission hang unsupported in the splined
                hubs of the clutch disc. Taking these precautions will prevent bending and distortion of the clutch
                disc.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the external clutch linkage before pulling the transmission free (
                    <hotlnk document="s11003_5.xml" xrefid="f1100313">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate cross shaft lever to allow yoke fingers to clear throw out bearing. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s11003_10.xml" xrefid="f1100346">Figure 46</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove transmission.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
